Mineral exploration and development company Kore Potash’s (Kore) lead project, the Kola sylvinite deposit (Kola), situated in the Republic of Congo, is progressing towards finalisation of the Definitive Feasibility Study (DFS) phase. Once the Greenfields project is operational, it is anticipated that it will be one of the lowest cost muriate of potash (MoP) producers globally, chairman David Hathorn tells Sascha Solomons. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 8 2018. It will be published online on the 10th September 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy